Analysis of the Target “Car” Image

•  Block Count and Layers  
  –  The model uses five total blocks if we count only the two visible wheels (rather than four).  
  –  There are two principal layers:  
     1)  The bottom layer, consisting of one long yellow rectangular block (forming the car’s “body”) plus the two horizontal orange cylinders (the “wheels”).  
     2)  The top layer, consisting of two cubes: one blue and one red.  

•  Spatial Arrangement  
  –  The long yellow rectangular block sits flat as the car’s base.  
  –  The two orange cylinders attach at the bottom, one on each side (left‐wheel and right‐wheel).  
  –  On top of the yellow base, the blue and red cubes sit side by side, forming the “cab” of the car.  

Selecting the Required Blocks from the Dictionary

1)  Yellow rectangular base → Dictionary block #6  
2)  Blue cube → Dictionary block #1  
3)  Red cube → Dictionary block #4  
4)  Two orange wheels → Dictionary blocks #13 and #14  
   - #13 for one horizontal wheel, and #14 for the other, matching the orientation seen in the target.  

Assembly Order

{  
  Step1: Move block with index 6   // Place the long yellow base  
  Step2: Move block with index 1   // Place the blue cube on top  
  Step3: Move block with index 4   // Place the red cube next to the blue  
  Step4: Move block with index 13  // Attach the first orange wheel horizontally  
  Step5: Move block with index 14  // Attach the second orange wheel horizontally  
}
